\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33363,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/05\/dawud-shukr-breath\/","url_meta":{"origin":27034,"position":3},"title":"Dawud on Gratitude: Hidden blessings are in each breath day and night","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Qurtubi reported: David, upon him be peace, said, \u201cO Lord, show me the hidden blessings upon me.\u201d Allah Almighty said, \u201cO David, breath,\u201d so David took a breath. Allah said, \u201cWho counts these blessings in each day and night?\u201d Source: Tafsi\u0304r al-Qurt\u0323ubi\u0304 2:52 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0637\u0628\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062f\u064e\u0627\u0648\u064f\u062f\u064f \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21430,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/12\/31\/natural-science-prophet-idrees\/","url_meta":{"origin":27034,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Idris: First to study natural sciences was Prophet Idris","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 31, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Mua\u2019wiyyah ibn al-Hakam reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, among us are men who write by script.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere was a prophet among the prophets who wrote by script. Whoever writes according to his way is correct.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31775,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/03\/malik-punishment-hard-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":27034,"position":5},"title":"Malik on Hearts: Worst punishment from Allah is having a hard heart","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Qurtubi reported: Malik ibn Dinar, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cA servant is not struck by a greater punishment than having a hard heart. Allah is not angry with people but that he removes mercy from their hearts.\u201d Source: Tafsi\u0304r al-Qurt\u0323ubi\u0304 39:22 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0637\u0628\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/27034","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=27034"}],"version-history"